      "date": "2019-03-01 19:00:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nElena - Thank you for the comment. Until a patch for LU-11743 lands, for separate MGS and MDS, a client is required on the MGS to manipulate pools. Without a client on the MGS, pool commands fail. Right now, there is no way around this that I know of.\nIn your comment, you say that we need to “find more appropriate way.” Do you mean that there is a different way to handle this in our test scripts or find a way to fix this in Lustre?",
