        "subject": "LU-8688 tests: start client on MGS for sanity tests",
        "message": "LU-8688 tests: start client on MGS for sanity tests\n\nWhen the Lustre file system has a separate MGS and MDS,\nwe need to start a client on the MGS when tests create\nor manipulate OST pools.\n\nMount the client on the MGS for sanity tests that deal\nwith OST pools. Add a trap for all these tests to\numount the client from the MGS using stack_trap().\n\nIn order for stack_trap() to work in these cases, we\nremoved the call to \"trap 0\" in destroy_test_pools.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: standalonemgs=true testlist=sanity,ost-pools\n\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <jnunez@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: If0c112edb90d309d9fdcf3a91d3cf85e589f1b59\n"
      },
